Daily Pilot: “Column: With artificial intelligence on the rise, humans should reconsider the way we think about our own” (Pierre Baldi interviewed)
August 21, 2019 
IBM’s Watson computer has already shown us that sophisticated machines can process, store and recall information faster and better than people. How can we prepare for a world in which computers are, in many ways, smarter than we are? 
I posed such questions to a local expert, Pierre Baldi, who has devoted his professional career to matters of intelligence — both human and artificial.
Read the full story here.
